data.chText: 在某时（不确切或尚未确定）
data.enText: at a time that you do not know exactly or has not yet been decided

data.chText: 我去年夏天什么时候见过他。
data.enText: I saw him sometime last summer.

data.chText: 我们一定要找个时间聚一下。
（指某人曾经是…）从前的，一度的
data.enText: used to refer to what sb used to be

data.chText: 本教区先前的牧师托马斯∙阿特金斯
data.enText: Thomas Atkins, sometime vicar of this parish
used to refer to what sb does occasionally

data.chText: 一位偶尔给本刊投稿的作者
data.enText: a sometime contributor to this magazine

means: 在某时(不确切或尚未确定)
(指某人曾经是…)从前的，一度的

tr: at some indefinite or unstated time
example: It was to be printed sometime later

value.def: You use sometime to refer to a time in the future or the past that is unknown or that has not yet been decided.

example.ex: The sales figures won't  be released until sometime next month...
example.tran: 下个月的某个时间才会公布销售数据。

example.ex: Why don't  you come and see me sometime?...
example.tran: 为什么不找个时间来看看我？

example.ex: I'm aiming to get to work by nine sometime...
example.tran: 我准备 9 点左右开始工作。

example.ex: I really want to go to Spain sometime.
example.tran: 我真的很想找个时间去趟西班牙。

gramarinfo.label: ADV with v, ADV with cl/group

value.def: You use sometime to describe a job or role that a person used to have.

example.ex: Cecile was in her early thirties, a sometime actress, dancer and singer.
example.tran: 塞茜尔三十出头，曾经做过演员、舞蹈演员和歌手。

value.tran: 前…(以前担任过某项职务)

value.boxu_tran: 切勿将 sometime 与 sometimes 混淆。
value.boxu_usage: Take care not to confuse sometime and sometimes
